# Apply security headers to everything; let Cloudflare Pages set sensible
# Cache-Control defaults for HTML (short cache, must-revalidate) and override
# only for /assets/* to opt those into long-cache. CF Pages concatenates
# matching rules' headers, so we can't safely set Cache-Control on /* without
# duplicating it on more specific paths.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=2592000, immutable
